INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (342651, 'Policy-makers continue to discover that they cannot solve today’s problems with yesterday’s mindsets', 16059, 0), (342652, 'That''s the thing about girls. Every time they do something pretty, even if they''re not much to look at, or even if they''re sort of stupid, you fall in love with them, and then you never know where the hell you are. Girls. Jesus Christ. They can drive you crazy. They really can.', 268, 0), (342653, 'You should write a book," Ron told Hermione as he cut up his potatoes, "translating mad things girls do so boys can understand them.', 28, 0), (342654, 'If a girl looks swell when she meets you, who gives a damn if she''s late?', 268, 0), (342655, 'We felt the imprisonment of being a girl, the way it made your mind active and dreamy, and how you ended up knowing which colors went together. We knew that the girls were our twins, that we all existed in space like animals with identical skins, and that they knew everything about us though we couldn’t fathom them at all. We knew, finally, that the girls were really women in disguise, that they understood love and even death, and that our job was merely to create the noise that seemed to fascinate them.', 680, 0), (342656, 'Well, wouldn''t it have been easier if she''d just asked me whether I liked her better than you?""Girls don''t often ask questions like that," said Hermione."Well, they should!" said Harry forcefully.', 28, 0), (342657, 'Girls do not dress for boys. They dress for themselves and, of course, each other. If girls dressed for boys they’d just walk around naked at all times.', 55837, 0), (342658, 'I don''t know," I said. "What else did you do for your first eighteen years?""Like I said," he said as I unlocked the car, "I''m not so sure that you should go by my example.""Why not?""Because I have my regrets," he said. "Also, I''m a guy. And guys do different stuff.""Like ride bikes?" I said."No," he replied. "Like have food fights. And break stuff. And set off firecrackers on people''s front porches. And...""Girls can''t set off firecrackers on people''s front porches?""They can," he said... "But they''re smart enough not to. That''s the difference.', 16, 0), (342659, 'That''s the pathetic thing about high school. Everyone tries so hard to be something they aren''t. It''s gotten so I don''t know who I am, so how can I even try to be who I am, much less who I''m not? My problem is that I don''t even fit in with the misfits. I don''t fit anywhere.', 12243, 0), (342660, 'She seemed glad to see me when I appeared in the kitchen, and by watching her I began to think there was some skill involved in being a girl.', 240, 0), (342661, 'You''re more trouble than you''re worth." "I''m a girl. That''s my job.', 2177, 0), (342662, 'But where do you live mostly now?"With the lost boys."Who are they?"They are the children who fall out of their perambulators when the nurse is looking the other way. If they are not claimed in seven days they are sent far away to the Neverland to defray expanses. I''m captain."What fun it must be!"Yes," said cunning Peter, "but we are rather lonely. You see we have no female companionship."Are none of the others girls?"Oh no; girls, you know, are much too clever to fall out of their prams.', 29, 0), (342663, 'That''s what they should teach us here. How girls'' brains work... It would be more useful than divination, anyway...', 28, 0), (342664, 'I think if you don''t really like a girl, you shouldn''t horse around with her at all, and if you do like her, then you''re supposed to like her face, and if you like her face, you ought to be careful about doing crumby stuff to it, like squirting water all over it. It''s really too bad that so much crumby stuff is a lot of fun sometimes.', 268, 0), (342665, 'I’m a wild girl from a cursed line of women. I paw at the ground and run under the moon. I like the feel of my own body. I’m not a slut or a nympho or someone who’s just