he kind of girl who wore dark lipstick and didn''t need to speak a word to seduce you.', 15134, 0), (342789, 'A woman that knows her worth doesn''t measure herself against another woman but stands strong, calmed and self confident.', 5089, 0), (342790, 'A beautiful girlfriend is worth two more.', 2892, 0), (342791, '... And what am I to do?""Well, that depends. Do you like the girl?""Like her? I don''t know. How do you know if...?""It''s very simple. Do you look at her furtively and feel like biting her?""Biting her?""On her backside, for example.', 252, 0), (342792, 'Females in general are embodiment of alluring mysteries that is beyond mortal capacity to decipher or understand.', 5089, 0), (342793, 'The talks were like blood transfusions, moments of realness and hope that were pinpricks of light in the dark fabric of small-town life.', 150, 0), (342794, 'These poor girls are just bad impersonators. They look cheap, really. There’s nothing special about them. They are just reaching out to get noticed. They don’t want to be invisible anymore. They don’t want to get lost in crowds.', 31718, 0), (342795, 'I`m kind of into girls so ya... sorry.', 48930, 0), (342796, 'Because you''re a girl and when a girl says she''s fine, she''s lying.', 20347, 0), (342797, 'I feel pretty sure I know why the dinosaurs went extinct. They were waiting for Sam to pick out a cell phone case.', 47824, 0), (342798, 'It’s just a party. You eat some food and drink a beer and pretend you don’t want to be crawdad fishing,” Angie said.	“No, it’s an echo chamber of sycophants and I can’t listen to some bimbo recite her newest purchases while pretending I don’t want to throw myself from the roof.', 31722, 0), (342799, 'I always reminded myself that this wasn''t exactly where I was meant to be, but pit stops are okay on the road of life, aren''t they?', 2250, 0), (342800, 'I love" is a door girls slam in their fathers'' faces.', 11553, 0);
